Introduction

Lily Jin Park Morrow is a South Korean-Australian singer-songwriter, dancer, and actress under JYP Entertainment. She is best known the oldest member and main vocalist of the girl group NMIXX.

In 2015 Lily participated in the fourth season of the reality show "K-pop Star" finishing in fourth place and signing a contract with JYP Entertainment.

On February 22, 2022. Lily made her debut as a member of NMIXX with their debut single album "AD MARE".
